This paper discusses the privacy concerns related to telemetry data collection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes new locally differentially private (LDP) mechanisms for repeated collection of counter data, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning (cs.DB, cs.LG). The paper also discusses the privacy guarantees provided by LDP algorithms, which is related to cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the empirical evaluation of the proposed mechanisms on real-world datasets, which falls under the category of computational science (cs.SI).
